{{Distinguish|Project Butter}} {{Infobox software | name = Butter Project | logo = GeZTZb2r.jpg | logo size = 128 | logo alt = Butter Project mascot | screenshot = | screenshot alt = | caption = A Streaming Tech Playground | collapsible = | author = | developer = | released = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | discontinued = | latest release version = | latest release date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | latest preview version = | latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | repo = {{bulleted list|{{URL|https://github.com/butterproject/butter-android}}|{{URL|https://github.com/butterproject/butter-desktop}}}} | programming language = [[HTML]], [[JavaScript]], [[Cascading Style Sheets|CSS]] | operating system = [[Linux]], [[OS X]], [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] | size = | language = | platform = [[Node.js]] | language count = 44 | language footnote = | genre = | license = [[GNU Affero General Public License]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://github.com/butterproject/butter-desktop/blob/devel/LICENSE|title=butter-desktop/LICENSE at devel · butterproject/butter-desktop|website=GitHub|language=en|access-date=2018-11-10}}</ref> | alexa = {{Decrease}} 942,884 ({{as of|2018|11|10|alt=Nov 2018}})<ref name=Alexa>{{cite web|title=Butterproject.org Traffic, Demographics and Competitors - Alexa|url=https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/butterproject.org|publisher=Alexa Internet, Inc|accessdate=10 Nov 2018}}</ref> | website = {{URL|https://butterproject.org}} | standard = | AsOf = }} {{file sharing sidebar}} '''Butter Project''' or simply '''Butter''' is a suite of [[Open-source software|open-source]] desktop and mobile applications that allow [[Streaming media|video-streaming]] over the [[BitTorrent]] protocol.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.yibada.com/articles/77626/20151025/popcorn-time-shutdown-was-the-result-of-outsiders-site-suffered-extensive-dns-attacks-and-tempering-developers-launch-project-butter.htm|title=Popcorn Time Shutdown Was The Result Of Outsiders, Site Suffered DNS Attacks And Tempering; Developers Launch Project Butter|date=2015-10-25|website=Yibada|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref> The project was first made public on 23 October 2015.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.inquisitr.com/2524990/video-streaming-service-popcorn-time-has-shut-down-in-lieu-of-project-butter/|title=Video Streaming Service Popcorn Time Has Shut Down In Lieu Of Project Butter|website=The Inquisitr News|access-date=2018-11-10}}</ref> The aim is to create a completely legal base which other applications can use to provide streaming functionality.<ref name=":0" />
Butter Project was created as a split from [[Popcorn Time]] when the latter met legal difficulties — with Butter Project aiming to retain development of only expressly legal and permissible portions of the code-base, relating to video-streaming. The developers have asserted Butter Project will not use any of the popcorntime.io infrastructure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mic.com/articles/127354/butter-project-streaming-service-and-the-latest-on-popcorn-time-shutdown#.CPCh1d0yE|title=Butter Project Streaming Service and the Latest On Popcorn Time Shutdown|last=Mic|website=Mic|access-date=2018-11-10}}</ref> Butter Project is not aimed at allowing copyright infringement, but aims to build the groundworks for streaming video over BitTorrent.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://thenextweb.com/apps/2015/10/23/popcorn-time-creators-back-away-from-copyrighted-content-with-project-butter/|title=Popcorn Time creators back away from copyrighted content with 'Project Butter'|last=Williams|first=Owen|website=The Next Web|language=en-US|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref> By having a legal portion which remains on [[GitHub]] the creators hope they can get more developers involved.<ref name=":1" />
By default Butter can play content from [[VODO]] which carries free videos, but will also be configurable to allow for custom sources of video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghacks.net/2015/10/23/makers-of-popcorn-time-launch-butter-project/|title=Makers of Popcorn Time launch Butter Project - gHacks Tech News|website=gHacks Technology News|language=en-US|access-date=2016-03-13}}</ref>
