{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox officeholder |name = Teresa Giménez Barbat |image = TeresaGBarbat.jpg |office = Member of [[European Parliament]] |president = |term_start = 25 November 2015 |term_end = |birth_name = María Teresa Giménez Barbat |birth_date = 4 June 1955 |birth_place = [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]] |party = [[Union, Progress and Democracy]] |otherparty = |occupation = Writer, [[anthropologist]], politician |website = {{URL|http://gimenezbarbat.com/}} }} '''María Teresa Giménez Barbat''' (born 4 June 1955 in Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain) is a Spanish [[anthropologist]], writer and politician. She advocates [[secular humanism]], rationalist universalism and [[scepticism]]. She writes in two languages, [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Catalan language|Catalan]]. She is member of the Spanish political party [[Union, Progress and Democracy]] (UPyD) and has participated in anti-nationalist movements before in [[Catalonia]].
== Biography == [[File:Teresa gimenez barbat.jpg|thumb|Teresa Giménez Barbat]] She studied at the [[University of Barcelona]], where she received a degree in anthropology. In 2008 she promoted the "Third Culture" association, and in 2009 "Secular Humanism Forum" dedicated to promote an ethic independent of religion.<ref>[http://www.humanismosecular.com/?p=1220 Presentación del Foro Humanismo Secular]</ref>
In 2006 she was a member of the directorate of the political party [[Citizens of Catalonia]], a new non-nationalist party. When UPyD was created with similar ideology, she joined the new formation, and since 2012, was a member of the directorate of the party in Catalonia. She was fifth in the UPyD list of candidates in the [[European Parliament election, 2009 (Spain)|2009 European Parliament Election]].<ref>[http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2009/06/02/barcelona/1243927227.html Entrevista en ''El Mundo'']</ref>
